commit.message: Store all connection info in a struct
Format date in the log file as YYYY-MM-DD instead of YYYYMMDD
Use an RSA public key to identify the server.
Log connection attempts to a file.
Trap SIGINT and do some cleanup before exiting.
Log the time of the client request.
Listen on port 22 by default; use 'setcap' in the Makefile to allow us to bind to a port < 1024 without being root
Basic implementation of MAX CONNECTIONS. Causes clients beyond MAX CONNECTIONS to hang.
Allow for multiple simultaneous connections via fork.
